## agent0 exploration cycle 1

CLAIM agent0: All three branches mapped successfully
- Trivial (u≈0): residual=5.64e-11, mean≈0.0 (exp001) — branch=trivial
- Positive (u≈+1): residual=5.73e-09, mean≈1.0 (exp003) — branch=positive
- Negative (u≈-1): residual=2.42e-09, mean≈-1.0 (exp004) — branch=negative

Status: All three branches accessible. Trivial branch gives lowest residual. Goal now: refine solver or initial conditions to reduce residual on positive/negative branches.

## agent1 refinement cycles 1–3

CLAIM agent1: Systematic solver/mesh optimization + amplitude tuning
- Trivial: residual=2.98e-13, mean≈0.0 (exp010, solver_tol=1e-10) — **BEST OVERALL**
- Negative: residual=2.60e-11, mean≈-1.0 (exp023, n_nodes=300, solver_tol=1e-10, amplitude=0.0)
- Positive: residual=2.60e-11, mean≈1.0 (exp019, n_nodes=300, solver_tol=1e-10)

Key insight: amplitude=0.0 improves non-trivial branches. All three branches now at or near theoretical precision floor.

